## Remarks  
 <span data-ttu-id="35619-117">Quando <xref:System.Runtime.InteropServices.SafeBuffer.AcquirePointer%2A> viene restituito, è consigliabile eseguire controllo verificando che dei limiti di `pointer` parametro `null`.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="35619-117">When <xref:System.Runtime.InteropServices.SafeBuffer.AcquirePointer%2A> returns, you should perform bounds checking by verifying that the `pointer` parameter is `null`.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="35619-118">Se non è `null`, è necessario chiamare il <xref:System.Runtime.InteropServices.SafeBuffer.ReleasePointer%2A?displayProperty=nameWithType> metodo in un'area a esecuzione vincolata (CER).</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="35619-118">If it is not `null`, you must call the <xref:System.Runtime.InteropServices.SafeBuffer.ReleasePointer%2A?displayProperty=nameWithType> method in a constrained execution region (CER).</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="35619-119"><xref:System.Runtime.InteropServices.SafeBuffer.AcquirePointer%2A> chiamate di <xref:System.Runtime.InteropServices.SafeHandle.DangerousAddRef%2A?displayProperty=nameWithType> metodo ed espone il puntatore.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="35619-119"><xref:System.Runtime.InteropServices.SafeBuffer.AcquirePointer%2A> calls the <xref:System.Runtime.InteropServices.SafeHandle.DangerousAddRef%2A?displayProperty=nameWithType> method and exposes the pointer.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="35619-120">A differenza di <xref:System.Runtime.InteropServices.SafeBuffer.Read%2A> metodo rimane invariata la posizione corrente dell'indicatore di misura.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="35619-120">Unlike the <xref:System.Runtime.InteropServices.SafeBuffer.Read%2A> method, it does not change the current position of the pointer.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="35619-121">Il seguente exampledemonstrates illustrato come utilizzare il <xref:System.Runtime.InteropServices.SafeBuffer.AcquirePointer%2A> metodo:</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="35619-121">The following exampledemonstrates how to use the <xref:System.Runtime.InteropServices.SafeBuffer.AcquirePointer%2A> method:</span></span>  
  
```  
byte* pointer = null;  
RuntimeHelpers.PrepareConstrainedRegions();  
try {  
    MySafeBuffer.AcquirePointer(ref pointer);  
    // Use pointer here, with your own bounds checking.  
    }  
finally {  
    if (pointer != null)  
        MySafeBuffer.ReleasePointer();  
    }  
```  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="35619-122">Se si esegue il cast `pointer` (ovvero un puntatore a un byte) come un puntatore a un tipo diverso (T \*), si potrebbero verificare problemi di allineamento di puntatore.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="35619-122">If you cast `pointer` (which is a pointer to a byte) as a pointer to a different type (T\*), you may have pointer alignment issues.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="35619-123">Devono assumersi la responsabilità per tutti i limiti di un controllo con l'indicatore di misura.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="35619-123">You must take responsibility for all bounds checking with this pointer.</span></span>

